---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
  <div class="privacy-container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 14, 2026</p>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Account Information</h3>
      <p>When you sign in with GitHub, we receive your GitHub username and email address. We use this information to identify you and associate your podcast generation requests with your account.</p>

      <h3>Usage Data</h3>
      <p>We collect information about the papers you submit for podcast generation, including arXiv URLs and generated content. This data is used to provide the service and improve its quality.</p>

      <h3>Crash Reports and Analytics</h3>
      <p>Our mobile applications collect crash reports and anonymized usage information. This data helps us identify and fix issues, and understand how users interact with the app. All usage data is anonymized and cannot be used to identify individual users. We use this information solely to improve the application.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain the Strollcast service</li>
        <li>To process your podcast generation requests</li>
        <li>To communicate with you about your requests</li>
        <li>To improve and optimize the service</li>
        <li>To identify and fix crashes and bugs in our mobile apps</li>
        <li>To understand how users interact with our apps and improve the user experience</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
      <p>Your data is stored securely using Cloudflare's infrastructure:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Database</strong> — Account and job metadata stored in Cloudflare D1</li>
        <li><strong>Audio Files</strong> — Generated podcasts stored in Cloudflare R2</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication</strong> — Handled via GitHub OAuth</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services to provide Strollcast:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>GitHub</strong> — For authentication</li>
        <li><strong>Anthropic Claude</strong> — For generating podcast scripts from papers</li>
        <li><strong>ElevenLabs</strong> — For text-to-speech audio generation</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — For hosting, storage, and content delivery</li>
        <li><strong>Firebase (Google)</strong> — For crash reporting and anonymized analytics in our mobile apps</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Each service has its own privacy policy governing how they handle data.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We only share data with third-party services as necessary to provide the Strollcast service (as described above).</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain your account information and generated podcasts indefinitely to provide the service. You may request deletion of your data by contacting us.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access your personal data</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent for data processing</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use essential cookies for authentication and session management. We do not use tracking or advertising cookies.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about this privacy policy, please open an issue on our <a href="https://github.com/strollcast/strollcast" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .privacy-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
</style>
